{"id": "EUVD-2025-20951", "enisaUuid": "57dd700e-df82-39a1-8e4e-277eb36468dd", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nPM: EM: Fix potential division-by-zero error in em_compute_costs()\n\nWhen the device is of a non-CPU type, table[i].performance won't be\ninitialized in the previous em_init_performance(), resulting in division\nby zero when calculating costs in em_compute_costs().\n\nSince the 'cost' algorithm is only used for EAS energy efficiency\ncalculations and is currently not utilized by other device drivers, we\nshould add the _is_cpu_device(dev) check to prevent this division-by-zero\nissue.", "datePublished": "2025-07-10T09:32:29", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T21:31:16", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/81d72f9241d884ec29524431f74f8009310cfa0c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/14cbdd64f3870cf0a2d94b87919b9056448c59a0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/179c0c7044a378198adb36f2a12410ab68cc730a", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38297"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38297"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "05ae7e22-4a87-3be9-86f0-744de233d455", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1b600da510735a0f92c8b4140a7e2cb037a6a6c3 <14cbdd64f3870cf0a2d94b87919b9056448c59a0"}, {"id": "2d039a37-ffe8-31b8-9afb-63a433deb7bd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.34"}, {"id": "441b586f-fd15-3b46-adad-963dec88e7dc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16-rc1"}, {"id": "4dcca78e-233e-3d4b-80f1-20bd2c450fda", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.3"}, {"id": "a07984a5-33c8-3284-97bd-b4e08aa6a3eb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1b600da510735a0f92c8b4140a7e2cb037a6a6c3 <81d72f9241d884ec29524431f74f8009310cfa0c"}, {"id": "d36d6150-6001-3438-a8aa-a31cd68f463d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "de55fd18-a8de-3b48-9887-a169501301